@NODE "What is it?"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Description @{fg text}@{bg back}

ami-dcraw is a port from Linux to M680x0 AmigaOS of dcraw version 8.70.

dcraw is a command-line ANSI C program to convert RAW photos from any digital camera on any computer running any operating system.
dcraw.c is written by Dave Coffin [ http://cybercom.net/~dcoffin/dcraw/ ] [ dcoffin@cybercom.net ].

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Requirements @{fg text}@{bg back}

A very fast Amiga with a large amount of RAM and at least a 68020 CPU and a 68881 FPU.
Alternatively an Amiga emulation package is required (Cloanto Amiga Forever recommended).

16 MegaPixels RAW files can require up to 256 MB to be converted.
Minimum stack size required is about 512000 bytes.

No particular installation is needed, you should be able to run the utility anywhere in your system.

Binary executables for specific CPUs are provided in the "Bin" directory.

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Usage @{fg text}@{bg back}

* Run with no arguments to see the following usage message:

Raw photo decoder "dcraw" v8.70
by Dave Coffin, dcoffin a cybercom o net

M680x0 AmigaOS port by:
Massimiliano Scarano   mscarano@libero.it
Domenico Lattanzi      domenico.lattanzi@domenicolattanzi.it

Usage:  ami-dcraw [OPTION]... [FILE]...

-v        Print verbose messages
-c        Write image data to standard output
-e        Extract embedded thumbnail image
-i        Identify files without decoding them
-i -v     Identify files and show metadata
-z        Change file dates to camera timestamp
-w        Use camera white balance, if possible
-a        Average the whole image for white balance
-A <x y w h> Average a grey box for white balance
-r <r g b g> Set custom white balance
-b <num>  Adjust brightness (default = 1.0)
-n <num>  Set threshold for wavelet denoising
-k <num>  Set black point
-K <file> Subtract dark frame (16-bit raw PGM)
-H [0-9]  Highlight mode (0=clip, 1=no clip, 2+=recover)
-t [0-7]  Flip image (0=none, 3=180, 5=90CCW, 6=90CW)
-o [0-5]  Output colorspace (raw,sRGB,Adobe,Wide,ProPhoto,XYZ)
-d        Document mode (no color, no interpolation)
-D        Document mode without scaling (totally raw)
-j        Don't stretch or rotate raw pixels
-q [0-3]  Set the interpolation quality
-h        Half-size color image (twice as fast as "-q 0")
-f        Interpolate RGGB as four colors
-s [0-99] Select a different raw image from the same file
-4        Write 16-bit linear instead of 8-bit with gamma
-T        Write TIFF instead of PPM

* See "Original_dcraw_V8_70/Manpage of dcraw.htm" for details.

* If you get a stack overflow error message, just modify the stack size using the stack command (stack 512000).

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Used platforms @{fg text}@{bg back}

Developed and tested on:
* Cloanto Amiga Forever 2006 Premium Edition, WinUAE 1.2.0, JIT, TCP/IP
* Some AmigaOS 3.9 and AmigaOS 3.5 files, ROM 3.1
* Kickstart 45.57, Workbench 45.3 (12/07/2001)
* System: 68020 68881 (INST: Cache)
* SAS/C Amiga Compiler 6.58 Copyright (c) 1988-1995 SAS Institute Inc.
* 1024 x 768 Workbench screen with 65536 colours (16 bit)

Tested on:
* Cloanto Amiga Forever 6, WinUAE 0.8.25 beta 1
* AmigaOS 3.5, ROM 3.1
* System: 68020 68881 (INST: Cache)
* Ram: 2 Mb Ram Chip, 0 Mb Ram Fast, 0 Mb Ram slow, 256 Mb Ram Z3-Fast
* Custom chip: ECS PAL Agnus (id=$0020), Normal Denise (id=$00FF)
* Kickstart version 45.57, Exec version 45.20, Disk version 45.3
* 800 x 600 Workbench screen with 256 colours (8 bit)

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Source code @{fg text}@{bg back}

Project files are located in the "Source" directory.

Compile with
"sc link lib:scm881.lib dcraw.c" (68020 + 68881)
"sc link lib:scm040.lib dcraw.c" (68040)

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Future improvements @{fg text}@{bg back}

We would like to make a picture datatype for Canon EOS 400D DIGITAL CR2 images out of ami-dcraw.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Limitations"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Known limitations @{fg text}@{bg back}

* The following untested cameras are expected not to be supported (lack of compiler 64-bit integers support):
    Kodak DCS Pro 14n
    Kodak DCS Pro 14nx
    Kodak DCS Pro SLR/c
    Kodak DCS Pro SLR/n
    Kodak DCS720X
    Kodak DCS760C
    Kodak DCS760M
    Kodak ProBack
    Kodak ProBack645
    Phase One P 25
    Phase One P 30
    Phase One P 45
    Polaroid x530
    SIGMA SD9
    SIGMA SD10
    SIGMA SD14

@ENDNODE



