@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Notes @{fg text}@{bg back}

* This is a port to a non GCC based compiler (SAS/C Amiga Compiler 6.58 Copyright (c) 1988-1995 SAS Institute Inc.).

* In the case of JPEG thumbs, dcraw adds an EXIF tag in CPU byte order.

* From platform to platform, even PPM output tends to differ in a few bytes,
  as dcraw uses floating-point math, and different FPUs have slightly different rounding rules.

* When saving tiff/ppm dcraw always saves something in cpu byte order for TIFF, never for PPM.

* The "-z" option works.

* AmigaOS wildcards work, as a result you can run the utility on a list of files.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Software changes"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Releases history @{fg text}@{bg back}

* Version 8.70 released 08-Jun-2007, first public release.

* Version 8.70 released 30-Jun-2007:
    * -z option added
    * AmigaOS wildcards added
    * few minor changes

* Version 8.70 released 16-Jul-2007:
    * recompiled with SAS/C 6.58
    * 68030 version replaced by the 68040 one
    * few minor changes

